  "text": "The CODEOWNERS infrastructure in grafana/grafana consists of five primary components:\n\n**1. GitHub Ownership Definition:**\n- `.github/CODEOWNERS`: The master file that defines team and user ownership of repository paths and files, following the standard GitHub CODEOWNERS format with patterns and @grafana teams.\n\n**2. CI/CD Validation:**\n- `.github/workflows/codeowners-validator.yml`: GitHub Actions workflow that automatically validates the CODEOWNERS file on every pull request, checking for file patterns, duplicate patterns, syntax errors, and identifying unowned files.\n\n**3. Manifest Generation Infrastructure (JavaScript):**\nThe `scripts/codeowners-manifest/` directory contains the manifest generation system that parses and indexes CODEOWNERS into queryable JSON files:\n\n- `constants.js`: Defines file paths for manifest outputs (teams.json, teams-by-filename.json, filenames-by-team.json, audit-raw.jsonl, metadata.json).\n- `raw.js`: Generates raw audit data by executing the github-codeowners CLI tool to produce JSONL output mapping files to their owners.\n- `metadata.js`: Creates metadata.json with SHA256 hashes of the CODEOWNERS file and git files for cache invalidation detection.\n- `generate.js`: Processes raw audit JSONL to generate three output JSON files: teams.json (list of all teams), teams-by-filename.json (which teams own each file), and filenames-by-team.json (which files each team owns).\n- `index.js`: Main orchestration script that coordinates the complete manifest generation pipeline with caching based on metadata hashes.\n\n**4. Go Feature Management Type System:**\n- `pkg/services/featuremgmt/codeowners.go`: Defines the `codeowner` string type for type-safe feature management and declares constants for all Grafana teams (e.g., @grafana/dashboards-squad, @grafana/alerting-squad, etc.) that match CODEOWNERS entries.\n- `pkg/services/featuremgmt/feature_toggle_api/types.go`: Defines FeatureSpec with the `Owner` field (JSON tag: \"codeowner\") to associate feature toggles with team ownership.\n- `pkg/services/featuremgmt/models.go`: Core feature management models and interfaces.\n\n**5. npm Scripts and Test Infrastructure:**\n- `package.json`: Contains orchestration scripts: `codeowners-manifest` (main generation), `codeowners-manifest:clean`, `codeowners-manifest:generate`, `codeowners-manifest:metadata`, `codeowners-manifest:raw` (individual stages), and `test:coverage:by-codeowner` (runs coverage for specific teams).\n- `jest.config.codeowner.js`: Jest configuration that filters test files and source code by team ownership, supporting team-specific test coverage reports.\n- `scripts/test-coverage-by-codeowner.js`: Test coverage orchestration script that runs Jest for a specific codeowner/team, generating coverage reports organized by team hierarchy.\n\nTogether, these components enable Grafana to maintain clear code ownership, automate validation, index ownership relationships for tooling, and generate team-specific test coverage metrics."
}

